race.comment: TOBA (7) won here and then found the grade a bit steep at Ipswich. Presented here again 4 days later, beaten 1.4L as favourite. Has had 16 days away this time and draws better. He can bounce back. INNERVISIONS (3) is in a top metro yard and has been threatening a win. Was slow off when beaten 3.3L at Doomben last time, and this is easier. Maps for a comfortable run and gets his chance in this company. LIGHTNING STRIKES (5) resumed at Kilcoy and did a good job to win a CL1 comfortably. Had no luck in a CL2 at Ipswich after and will be better for that. He has more to offer and has claims. PINTURA ROSA (12) has been off the scene for 287 days, but she has the ability and has had a couple of recent trials. May need one, but a betting watch is advised.
